Gauteng's most wanted suspect, Mbuso Ndabazovela Biyela, has been killed in a shootout with police in KwaZulu-Natal.  JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng’s most-wanted suspect, Mbuso Ndabazovela Biyela, has been killed in KwaZulu-Natal during a shootout with police. Biyela was wanted for eight cases, including the murder of a police officer. A joint team conducted a takedown operation in Weenen, KwaZulu-Natal in the early hours of Monday morning. Biyela fired shots at officers as they approached the house in which he was hiding. He was arrested twice in 2020 and 2021 but managed to escape. Biyela was positively linked to five murders in Soweto and KwaZulu-Natal and a hijacking. A reward of R100,000 was offered in May for information on his whereabouts.